<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[775,1399,792,1409]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
Note. Since the 
<typeStatus box="[983,1024,793,812]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1902" box="[1148,1323,792,811]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Admestina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis box="[1148,1323,792,811]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Admestina insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been examined, the synonymy is established based on the very good illustrations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1976" box="[972,1103,852,871]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="otiosa">
<emphasis box="[972,1103,852,871]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">Helvetia otiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="GALIANO" box="[1139,1273,852,872]" firstAuthor="GALIANO" journalOrPublisher="Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" pagination="51 - 56" part="35" refId="ref6535" refString="GALIANO, M. E. 1976. Dos nuevas especies del genero Helvetia Peckham, 1894 (Araneae, Salticidae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 35: 51 - 56." title="Dos nuevas especies del genero Helvetia Peckham, 1894 (Araneae, Salticidae)" type="journal article" year="1976">GALIANO (1976</bibRefCitation>
, figs 8-12).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="142" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[775,1399,792,1409]" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">
Diagnosis. The male of this species is easily dintinguished from the remaining species of the genus by the very long embolus, the form of the RTA and the presence of a depression on the retrolateral cymbium where the tip of the embolus is held in resting position (see 
<bibRefCitation author="GALIANO" box="[1015,1151,1001,1021]" firstAuthor="GALIANO" journalOrPublisher="Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" pagination="51 - 56" part="35" refId="ref6535" refString="GALIANO, M. E. 1976. Dos nuevas especies del genero Helvetia Peckham, 1894 (Araneae, Salticidae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 35: 51 - 56." title="Dos nuevas especies del genero Helvetia Peckham, 1894 (Araneae, Salticidae)" type="journal article" year="1976">GALIANO 1976</bibRefCitation>
, figs 10-11). Females are very like those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peckham &amp; Peckham" authorityYear="1894" box="[952,1079,1032,1051]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santarema">
<emphasis box="[952,968,1032,1050]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[981,1079,1032,1050]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">santarema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the medial posterior fusion of the copulatory openings, like that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustavo R. S. Ruiz &amp; Antonio D. Brescovit" authorityYear="2008" box="[802,897,1091,1111]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Helvetia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="142" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labiata">
<emphasis box="[802,818,1092,1110]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[831,897,1091,1110]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="142">labiata</emphasis>
